1
00:00:00,257 --> 00:00:01,551
There!

2
00:00:03,138 --> 00:00:04,765
Got it!

3
00:00:05,100 --> 00:00:06,728
Nice catch!

4
00:00:06,811 --> 00:00:08,815
Wow, Shinpei-san, you're amazing!

5
00:00:09,400 --> 00:00:12,406
Alright, next up...
Conan-kun!

6
00:00:12,489 --> 00:00:14,160
Here goes! There!

7
00:00:18,418 --> 00:00:19,795
Huh? Whoa...

8
00:00:21,299 --> 00:00:22,676
Ah...
Huh?

9
00:00:23,470 --> 00:00:25,057
Huh? Whoa, whoa!

10
00:00:26,184 --> 00:00:29,273
H-Hey, come on...
Cut it out!

11
00:00:30,317 --> 00:00:31,945
Huh... Matsunosuke?

12
00:00:32,029 --> 00:00:33,239
Matsunosuke?

13
00:00:33,908 --> 00:00:35,577
Stop that, Matsunosuke!

14
00:00:37,999 --> 00:00:39,920
(Matsunosuke barks)

15
00:00:41,130 --> 00:00:42,926
Good morning, Granny!

16
00:00:43,009 --> 00:00:44,095
Granny?

17
00:00:44,595 --> 00:00:46,432
Shinpei... You..

18
00:00:46,516 --> 00:00:48,938
Are you messing around again instead of working?
First thing in the morning?

19
00:00:49,772 --> 00:00:52,111
Messing around? I wasn't really...

20
00:00:52,194 --> 00:00:54,365
He isn't messing around.

21
00:00:54,448 --> 00:00:58,248
He teaches us frisbee here every week!

22
00:00:58,331 --> 00:01:00,962
He's super nice!
Heheh...

23
00:01:01,212 --> 00:01:04,635
That's the same as messing around.
A grown man like you...

24
00:01:04,719 --> 00:01:07,182
Thanks to that, now even Matsunosuke...

25
00:01:07,599 --> 00:01:09,019
Tries to catch anything that looks like a frisbee.

26
00:01:09,103 --> 00:01:10,105
(Matsunosuke barks)

27
00:01:10,397 --> 00:01:14,155
That dog's name is Matsunosuke?
So cute!

28
00:01:14,238 --> 00:01:16,659
Oh dear, you're all covered in mud...

29
00:01:16,743 --> 00:01:17,996
Hm?
Ah...

30
00:01:18,079 --> 00:01:20,125
Let me clean this up properly...
Huh?

31
00:01:20,208 --> 00:01:21,210
Here, I'll give it back.

32
00:01:21,294 --> 00:01:24,216
Oh, it's fine... This is no big deal.

33
00:01:24,300 --> 00:01:27,723
No, I can't let it be.
These things need to be done properly.

34
00:01:27,806 --> 00:01:31,397
I don't want your parents
complaining at me later.

35
00:01:31,814 --> 00:01:36,073
Granny, you're about to have breakfast, right?
Let me eat too!

36
00:01:37,117 --> 00:01:41,042
Once you do some proper work
and pay back the money I lent you.

37
00:01:41,459 --> 00:01:44,048
Ugh... Fine... Sigh...

38
00:01:51,270 --> 00:01:57,282
♪~

39
00:02:04,296 --> 00:02:07,929
Black shadows and pitch-black darkness...
The light of deduction cuts right through.

40
00:02:08,012 --> 00:02:12,104
Same morning walk with the beloved dog, day after day...
A tiny difference sparks the beginning of a case.

41
00:02:12,187 --> 00:02:13,648
Seeing through the one and only truth...

42
00:02:13,731 --> 00:02:15,443
A child's appearance, an adult's mind...

43
00:02:15,527 --> 00:02:18,241
His name is Detective Conan!

44
00:03:40,030 --> 00:03:46,042
~♪

45
00:03:49,704 --> 00:03:53,704
"Suspicious Promenade"

46
00:03:53,704 --> 00:03:58,566
(doorbell rings)

47
00:04:00,891 --> 00:04:02,437
(doorbell rings)

48
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:05,318
Is Granny home?

49
00:04:05,401 --> 00:04:07,822
We came to pick up Conan's clothes!

50
00:04:08,072 --> 00:04:09,701
Looks like she's not here.

51
00:04:09,784 --> 00:04:11,538
Probably walking the dog, right?

52
00:04:11,621 --> 00:04:14,127
Yeah... We'll come back later.

53
00:04:14,210 --> 00:04:17,550
But it looks like Matsunosuke
is sleeping over there.

54
00:04:18,135 --> 00:04:19,596
You're right.

55
00:04:19,971 --> 00:04:24,606
Sleeping so peacefully...
Not moving at all.

56
00:04:24,689 --> 00:04:27,487
Oh my, is he sleeping? Matsunosuke!

57
00:04:28,071 --> 00:04:30,868
And here I was,
about to give him a treat...

58
00:04:30,951 --> 00:04:32,789
Um, who's that lady?

59
00:04:33,207 --> 00:04:35,461
She's Kanae-san's dog friend.
- Hirota Tomoko (52), Kanae's dog friend.

60
00:04:35,544 --> 00:04:37,632
She owns one of Matsunosuke's
siblings.

61
00:04:37,715 --> 00:04:42,015
What?! Matsunosuke has siblings?
Do they look alike?

62
00:04:42,099 --> 00:04:44,103
Of course. They're identical.

63
00:04:50,658 --> 00:04:52,412
Hey... Don't tell me...

64
00:04:53,705 --> 00:04:54,791
Hm?
Conan-kun?

65
00:04:58,340 --> 00:04:59,634
Is it unlocked?

66
00:05:01,346 --> 00:05:04,310
Ah... Ugh...
Kyaa!

67
00:05:05,271 --> 00:05:06,690
K-Kanae-san!

68
00:05:08,235 --> 00:05:10,448
What on earth is all this racket?!

69
00:05:10,531 --> 00:05:11,992
I can't concentrate with all this noise...

70
00:05:12,075 --> 00:05:13,704
Ugh... Ahh!

71
00:05:20,426 --> 00:05:23,390
So when we came to get Conan's clothes...

72
00:05:23,474 --> 00:05:26,020
Matsunosuke was asleep.

73
00:05:26,103 --> 00:05:28,024
No matter how much we called, he wouldn't wake up.

74
00:05:28,107 --> 00:05:30,529
Huh? M-Matsunosuke?

75
00:05:30,905 --> 00:05:34,162
He's a dog. Sleeping in the doghouse outside.

76
00:05:34,245 --> 00:05:39,130
Ah... Forensics says it looks like
he was put to sleep with some kind of drug.

77
00:05:39,214 --> 00:05:40,549
Drug?

78
00:05:40,841 --> 00:05:44,891
Now then... You're Hirota-san,
the fellow dog owner, correct?

79
00:05:45,309 --> 00:05:49,567
Yes. I came to share
some dog treats, but...

80
00:05:49,651 --> 00:05:50,778
And then this...

81
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:55,287
...And you are the neighbor, Kitazawa-san.

82
00:05:55,704 --> 00:05:59,128
Yeah. The doorbell next door kept ringing over and over...
- Kitazawa Soukichi (54), Kanae's neighbor.

83
00:05:59,212 --> 00:06:01,299
So I came to see what was going on,
and found this.

84
00:06:01,633 --> 00:06:04,764
Are the two of you acquainted?

85
00:06:05,474 --> 00:06:06,601
We know each other.

86
00:06:07,144 --> 00:06:09,148
Hirota-san...

87
00:06:09,150 --> 00:06:11,820
Didn't you borrow quite a bit of money
from Kanae-san?

88
00:06:11,903 --> 00:06:13,949
She was always complaining about it.

89
00:06:14,032 --> 00:06:17,038
Saying you never paid her back at all.

90
00:06:17,123 --> 00:06:19,752
Maybe you're the culprit, hmm?

91
00:06:19,836 --> 00:06:23,802
I heard you were always
complaining too.

92
00:06:23,885 --> 00:06:26,015
That the dog's yapping
was too noisy.

93
00:06:26,433 --> 00:06:30,274
What... Are you saying I'm the culprit?
Don't be ridiculous!

94
00:06:30,357 --> 00:06:31,901
Right back at you!

95
00:06:31,985 --> 00:06:33,697
Now, now, calm down.

96
00:06:34,407 --> 00:06:38,915
Inspector Megure. Between 8 AM
and 8:15 AM...

97
00:06:38,999 --> 00:06:41,755
Several people in the shopping district
and the park...

98
00:06:41,838 --> 00:06:45,638
Reportedly saw Asakawa-san
walking her dog.

99
00:06:45,721 --> 00:06:50,356
Hmm... Do you happen to know
Asakawa-san's walking route?

100
00:06:50,648 --> 00:06:53,320
If I recall, she leaves the house,
goes through the shopping district...

101
00:06:53,403 --> 00:06:54,947
Then heads to the park.

102
00:06:55,031 --> 00:06:58,538
After that, she said she comes back
along the main road.

103
00:06:58,622 --> 00:07:01,544
Yes. She always said
about an hour long walk...

104
00:07:01,628 --> 00:07:03,674
Was the best routine for them.

105
00:07:03,924 --> 00:07:05,219
Which means...

106
00:07:05,302 --> 00:07:08,141
She left the house a little before 8 AM...

107
00:07:08,225 --> 00:07:11,940
Finished the walk, and returned home
around 9 AM.

108
00:07:12,191 --> 00:07:15,447
So she was killed after that.

109
00:07:15,823 --> 00:07:17,910
What were you two doing during that time?

110
00:07:18,662 --> 00:07:21,793
I was at home, playing shogi
with an acquaintance.

111
00:07:22,211 --> 00:07:24,298
I was at home too.

112
00:07:24,757 --> 00:07:27,053
I had flowers delivered
from the florist...

113
00:07:27,138 --> 00:07:30,394
And asked them to arrange them
on the spot.

114
00:07:31,855 --> 00:07:35,571
My jacket came back
from the cleaners.

115
00:07:36,656 --> 00:07:37,658
Hm?

116
00:07:46,342 --> 00:07:48,513
Hmm... Ah!

117
00:07:58,241 --> 00:08:00,454
A beige
spring coat.

118
00:08:00,537 --> 00:08:03,460
The coat she was wearing
when she died, huh... Hm?

119
00:08:03,960 --> 00:08:07,218
A pack of prepared food...
Her breakfast?

120
00:08:07,301 --> 00:08:10,224
Huh? But Shinpei-san, back then...

121
00:08:10,307 --> 00:08:12,561
Inspector, come here!
Hm...

122
00:08:13,688 --> 00:08:15,567
What is it?
Look at this.

123
00:08:15,943 --> 00:08:17,655
A bandana, huh?

124
00:08:17,738 --> 00:08:20,244
Oh! Is that stain blood?

125
00:08:20,619 --> 00:08:23,040
Hey, isn't that...
Yeah.

126
00:08:23,583 --> 00:08:25,712
Shinpei-san's bandana.

127
00:08:26,004 --> 00:08:27,675
Shinpei-san?

128
00:08:27,758 --> 00:08:29,345
He's Kanae-san's grandson.

129
00:08:29,428 --> 00:08:31,224
Inspector Megure!
Hm?

130
00:08:31,683 --> 00:08:35,148
This person says she saw a man
running out of this house...

131
00:08:35,232 --> 00:08:37,570
What?
Sorry...

132
00:08:37,653 --> 00:08:40,284
Could you tell us
what you just said once more?

133
00:08:40,367 --> 00:08:41,536
Yes.

134
00:08:41,911 --> 00:08:44,500
I think it was just past 9 AM...

135
00:08:44,584 --> 00:08:47,256
A young man
came out of this house.

136
00:08:47,798 --> 00:08:50,262
His face was deathly pale,
like he was running away.

137
00:08:50,888 --> 00:08:54,562
I'm pretty sure that person was
Kanae-san's grandson...

138
00:08:54,645 --> 00:08:59,029
Hmm. Do you know
where he lives?

139
00:08:59,112 --> 00:09:02,661
I heard he lives alone
in an apartment nearby.

140
00:09:02,745 --> 00:09:05,500
Right. Let's bring him in for questioning
immediately.

141
00:09:05,584 --> 00:09:07,129
R-Right.

142
00:09:07,880 --> 00:09:08,882
No way...

143
00:09:08,965 --> 00:09:11,638
There's no way Shinpei-san
would commit murder.

144
00:09:11,721 --> 00:09:13,516
It has to be some kind of mistake!

145
00:09:16,522 --> 00:09:19,946
This is awful...
Shinpei-san, a murderer?

146
00:09:20,029 --> 00:09:24,079
Even though he teaches us frisbee
so enthusiastically...

147
00:09:24,413 --> 00:09:26,501
No way... Absolutely not.

148
00:09:26,584 --> 00:09:27,878
(stomach growls)

149
00:09:28,254 --> 00:09:29,548
Hey, Genta-kun!

150
00:09:29,632 --> 00:09:32,011
What's wrong with you, at a time like this?

151
00:09:32,095 --> 00:09:34,225
I-It wasn't me!

152
00:09:34,308 --> 00:09:36,896
(stomach growls)
Sigh... Huh?

153
00:09:37,272 --> 00:09:38,274
Shinpei-san!

154
00:09:38,358 --> 00:09:40,069
Ah, Conan-kun!

155
00:09:40,612 --> 00:09:43,576
Hey, you...
The police are looking for you.

156
00:09:44,286 --> 00:09:46,290
This is about Granny, right?

157
00:09:46,582 --> 00:09:50,298
Yeah. They're saying Shinpei-san
is the culprit.

158
00:09:51,801 --> 00:09:54,055
No... I didn't do it.

159
00:09:54,557 --> 00:09:57,563
But Shinpei-san,
you ran away from the scene, right?

160
00:09:58,148 --> 00:10:02,239
Th-That's... Granny called me over
with a text...

161
00:10:02,322 --> 00:10:03,825
And when I got there, she was already...

162
00:10:03,908 --> 00:10:06,664
I ran outside in a panic
and bumped into someone...

163
00:10:06,748 --> 00:10:09,587
After that, I just...
I didn't know what was happening...

164
00:10:10,130 --> 00:10:12,676
Shinpei-san... You said your grandmother
has breakfast...

165
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:15,265
After walking Matsunosuke, right?

166
00:10:15,348 --> 00:10:17,478
Huh? Ah... Yeah.

167
00:10:17,561 --> 00:10:20,734
She always said eating after a little exercise
felt better.

168
00:10:20,817 --> 00:10:22,111
There he is!

169
00:10:23,907 --> 00:10:26,788
No! It wasn't me!

170
00:10:28,333 --> 00:10:32,966
(police siren)

171
00:10:33,050 --> 00:10:35,764
They arrested Shinpei-san...

172
00:10:35,847 --> 00:10:37,392
Hey, Conan-kun...

173
00:10:37,476 --> 00:10:39,146
Why are you just letting this happen?!

174
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:41,192
There's nothing we can do.

175
00:10:41,275 --> 00:10:43,863
Shinpei-san's bandana
was found at the scene...

176
00:10:43,947 --> 00:10:45,659
And there's even an eyewitness.

177
00:10:45,742 --> 00:10:47,412
No way...

178
00:10:47,496 --> 00:10:50,836
Conan-kun, you think
Shinpei-san is the culprit too?

179
00:10:50,919 --> 00:10:52,297
I misjudged you.

180
00:10:52,381 --> 00:10:53,967
But...
Hm?

181
00:10:54,677 --> 00:10:57,891
There's more to what you're saying,
isn't there? Edogawa-kun.

182
00:10:57,975 --> 00:10:58,977
Well, yeah.

183
00:10:59,645 --> 00:11:03,945
First, the bandana found at the scene
isn't that rare of an item...

184
00:11:04,028 --> 00:11:06,993
If someone wanted one,
they could get one easily.

185
00:11:07,076 --> 00:11:11,252
I see... So the real culprit
might have prepared it...

186
00:11:11,335 --> 00:11:13,798
To pin the crime on Shinpei-san.

187
00:11:13,882 --> 00:11:15,385
But that alone isn't enough...

188
00:11:16,052 --> 00:11:18,015
Inside the trash can at the scene...

189
00:11:18,098 --> 00:11:21,981
There was a plastic bag
with a dry cleaning tag on it.

190
00:11:22,064 --> 00:11:23,443
On that tag...

191
00:11:23,526 --> 00:11:27,910
It said "Women's beige spring coat."

192
00:11:27,993 --> 00:11:30,540
A beige spring coat?

193
00:11:30,624 --> 00:11:34,088
Ah! The coat Granny was wearing
when she died!

194
00:11:34,381 --> 00:11:37,846
Right. And then,
underneath that plastic bag...

195
00:11:37,930 --> 00:11:40,810
A breakfast prepared food pack
had been thrown away.

196
00:11:40,894 --> 00:11:44,151
The breakfast pack was under the plastic bag...

197
00:11:44,235 --> 00:11:47,574
Which means the breakfast pack
was thrown away first.

198
00:11:47,658 --> 00:11:51,958
So she ate breakfast,
then went to walk Matsunosuke.

199
00:11:52,876 --> 00:11:54,797
Ah, that's backwards!
Yes, it's reversed!

200
00:11:55,131 --> 00:11:59,390
Exactly. According to Shinpei-san,
the old lady always...

201
00:11:59,473 --> 00:12:03,356
Had breakfast after coming back
from walking Matsunosuke...

202
00:12:03,439 --> 00:12:06,111
But the scene showed
the opposite.

203
00:12:06,195 --> 00:12:10,161
In other words, the scene
may have been staged.

204
00:12:10,620 --> 00:12:14,545
But what if Shinpei-san
is the one lying?

205
00:12:14,628 --> 00:12:15,922
No chance of that.

206
00:12:16,424 --> 00:12:20,390
He talked about his grandmother's breakfast
last week too, remember?

207
00:12:20,849 --> 00:12:25,107
Granny, you're about to have breakfast, right?
Let me eat too!

208
00:12:25,483 --> 00:12:28,113
If he'd been lying
since back then...

209
00:12:28,197 --> 00:12:29,825
That'd be pretty premeditated.

210
00:12:29,908 --> 00:12:33,499
A guy that calculating wouldn't
drop a bloodstained bandana, right?

211
00:12:33,583 --> 00:12:34,835
Good point.

212
00:12:35,128 --> 00:12:36,964
Then who on earth...

213
00:12:37,048 --> 00:12:38,843
As far as suspects go right now...

214
00:12:38,926 --> 00:12:41,849
There's the dog friend Hirota-san
and the neighbor Kitazawa-san.

215
00:12:41,932 --> 00:12:44,271
But they both
have alibis...

216
00:12:44,355 --> 00:12:47,486
Then let's tear those alibis
to shreds ourselves!

217
00:12:47,569 --> 00:12:49,406
Right! If we do that...

218
00:12:49,490 --> 00:12:52,162
Shinpei-san might be able
to come back.

219
00:12:52,245 --> 00:12:54,500
Time for the Detective Boys to shine!

220
00:12:54,583 --> 00:12:55,627
Yes!
Yeah!

221
00:12:55,710 --> 00:12:57,255
First up, Kitazawa-san's place.

222
00:12:57,339 --> 00:12:59,718
Then we'll ask around
the shopping district.

223
00:12:59,802 --> 00:13:00,845
Yeah!

224
00:13:10,460 --> 00:13:11,879
Hmm...

225
00:13:11,963 --> 00:13:13,340
No take-backs.

226
00:13:13,591 --> 00:13:16,221
Shut up... I know that.

227
00:13:16,304 --> 00:13:18,058
Here goes, Conan! There!

228
00:13:18,142 --> 00:13:19,352
Ahh!

229
00:13:22,609 --> 00:13:23,945
Sorry!

230
00:13:24,028 --> 00:13:27,160
Our frisbee went in there...
Could you get it for us?

231
00:13:27,243 --> 00:13:28,245
Good grief...

232
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:29,832
Sorry!

233
00:13:29,915 --> 00:13:33,005
Alright, alright.
Go around to the front door.

234
00:13:33,506 --> 00:13:34,508
Hmm...

235
00:13:34,592 --> 00:13:37,723
Sorry about that, mister.
Our frisbee...

236
00:13:37,806 --> 00:13:39,560
Oh, shogi!

237
00:13:39,643 --> 00:13:42,356
Hmm, looks like a close match.

238
00:13:42,441 --> 00:13:43,902
How long have you been playing?

239
00:13:44,194 --> 00:13:46,323
Heh... Since this morning.

240
00:13:46,574 --> 00:13:48,787
Wow, that's amazing.

241
00:13:48,870 --> 00:13:52,251
99 wins, 99 losses over 10 years.

242
00:13:52,335 --> 00:13:54,507
Today's the day we settle it once and for all.

243
00:13:55,049 --> 00:13:59,642
We've been battling since 6 AM
without a single break, but...

244
00:13:59,725 --> 00:14:01,521
Looks like you're losing.
Ugh...

245
00:14:01,813 --> 00:14:04,234
Shut up! Don't interrupt the match!

246
00:14:04,485 --> 00:14:07,658
S-Sorry...
Hmph!

247
00:14:08,158 --> 00:14:12,208
Yes, 8:30.
At that time, Hirota-san...

248
00:14:12,291 --> 00:14:15,715
Asked me to deliver the flowers,
so I went over.

249
00:14:15,799 --> 00:14:18,930
And the arrangement as well?
Yes.

250
00:14:19,013 --> 00:14:20,600
There were so many flowers...

251
00:14:20,684 --> 00:14:23,021
In the end, it took me
until past noon.

252
00:14:23,272 --> 00:14:24,859
Is that so...

253
00:14:27,656 --> 00:14:30,787
In the end, we couldn't
break the alibis.

254
00:14:30,871 --> 00:14:33,083
What do we do now, Conan?

255
00:14:33,166 --> 00:14:35,547
Shinpei-san's going to be framed for this.

256
00:14:35,881 --> 00:14:37,133
Hmm...

257
00:14:37,216 --> 00:14:41,016
Maybe our original premise
was wrong.

258
00:14:41,266 --> 00:14:43,605
Huh? original premise?

259
00:14:44,565 --> 00:14:46,192
We've been thinking the victim,
the old lady...

260
00:14:46,276 --> 00:14:50,619
Was killed after returning
from walking Matsunosuke, but...

261
00:14:50,911 --> 00:14:53,123
Huh?
What do you mean?

262
00:14:53,541 --> 00:14:58,425
The old lady walked the same route
at nearly the same time every morning.

263
00:14:59,010 --> 00:15:00,931
So... maybe...

264
00:15:01,557 --> 00:15:04,062
I see... The witnesses...

265
00:15:04,145 --> 00:15:06,651
Just assumed they saw her
this morning as well.

266
00:15:06,734 --> 00:15:08,111
Yeah.

267
00:15:08,195 --> 00:15:11,409
An old lady in a beige coat
walking a dog, right?

268
00:15:11,494 --> 00:15:13,706
I saw her this morning too.

269
00:15:13,790 --> 00:15:15,292
Was it really this morning?

270
00:15:15,710 --> 00:15:18,340
Yeah, a little past 8, I think.

271
00:15:18,423 --> 00:15:21,514
I always pass her
when I'm walking this guy.

272
00:15:22,056 --> 00:15:25,772
That dog always
marks his territory right there...

273
00:15:26,106 --> 00:15:28,861
But this morning, that person
seemed to be in a hurry...

274
00:15:28,945 --> 00:15:31,199
She just dragged the dog
right past.

275
00:15:31,784 --> 00:15:35,667
Ah, the lady who walks her dog
every morning, right?

276
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:38,923
I saw her. This morning
was especially bad.

277
00:15:39,007 --> 00:15:40,175
Especially bad?

278
00:15:40,468 --> 00:15:44,392
That dog always gets in a fight
with a cat in front of my shop.

279
00:15:44,810 --> 00:15:46,897
This morning it was really awful.

280
00:15:47,441 --> 00:15:48,818
Lately, that person...

281
00:15:48,901 --> 00:15:51,490
Had been keeping the dog
away from the cat, but...

282
00:15:51,574 --> 00:15:53,870
Seems like she got careless.

283
00:15:55,498 --> 00:15:58,086
So far, that's exactly 15 minutes
from the house.

284
00:15:58,170 --> 00:16:01,051
Everyone said
she passed by this morning.

285
00:16:01,134 --> 00:16:05,267
Hmm... So that means
it wasn't just an assumption.

286
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:08,106
Hmm... Huh?

287
00:16:10,779 --> 00:16:13,033
Excuse me, ma'am.

288
00:16:13,116 --> 00:16:15,245
Yes? What is it?

289
00:16:15,329 --> 00:16:19,253
Did you see a woman walking a dog
around here this morning?

290
00:16:19,337 --> 00:16:23,471
Oh, the police asked me
the same thing.

291
00:16:23,554 --> 00:16:25,934
I saw her. Definitely.

292
00:16:26,267 --> 00:16:29,817
Was that person
dragging the dog along?

293
00:16:29,900 --> 00:16:34,200
Dragging? Yes...
Something like that.

294
00:16:34,785 --> 00:16:38,459
When that person leaves the park,
she always goes left.

295
00:16:38,543 --> 00:16:40,170
But this morning...

296
00:16:40,420 --> 00:16:42,968
She pulled the dog and went right.

297
00:16:43,970 --> 00:16:45,473
Pulled the dog... to the right?

298
00:16:45,723 --> 00:16:47,351
H-Hey, Conan-kun!

299
00:16:47,602 --> 00:16:50,107
This is the opposite direction
from the walking route!

300
00:16:50,190 --> 00:16:52,612
We won't find any witnesses
this way!

301
00:16:52,696 --> 00:16:54,407
(dog barks)
Ah!

302
00:16:58,039 --> 00:16:59,877
Th-This is...

303
00:17:00,545 --> 00:17:02,591
Oh? You kids...
Hm?

304
00:17:03,091 --> 00:17:05,555
Still looking for witnesses?

305
00:17:05,638 --> 00:17:06,724
Hm?

306
00:17:06,807 --> 00:17:09,312
Ah! That guy from earlier!

307
00:17:09,395 --> 00:17:11,984
Didn't recognize you
without your dog.

308
00:17:12,067 --> 00:17:13,153
Ha...

309
00:17:13,236 --> 00:17:16,493
I see... So that's how it is.

310
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:19,415
Everyone was mistaken.

311
00:17:19,499 --> 00:17:23,006
The witnesses... and even the culprit.

312
00:17:24,425 --> 00:17:27,891
If that's the case, the culprit
will definitely show up there.

313
00:17:29,978 --> 00:17:33,151
To destroy the crucial evidence.

314
00:17:42,837 --> 00:17:44,549
Good evening.

315
00:17:47,346 --> 00:17:49,726
What's the matter? At this hour...

316
00:17:50,143 --> 00:17:51,855
You children...

317
00:17:52,356 --> 00:17:57,241
Lady, we've figured out
who the real culprit is...

318
00:17:57,617 --> 00:17:59,161
The one who killed Kanae-san.

319
00:17:59,245 --> 00:18:00,414
What...

320
00:18:00,873 --> 00:18:04,297
The culprit killed Kanae-san
well before 8 AM this morning...

321
00:18:04,380 --> 00:18:08,013
Right after she'd finished
preparing breakfast.

322
00:18:08,597 --> 00:18:12,229
After that, they cleaned up
the breakfast that had been set out...

323
00:18:12,313 --> 00:18:16,070
Dressed the body in the coat
that had just come back from the cleaners...

324
00:18:16,572 --> 00:18:20,329
And made it look like she was killed
after returning from her walk.

325
00:18:20,412 --> 00:18:23,961
Then, they placed Shinpei-san's bandana,
which they'd prepared beforehand...

326
00:18:24,378 --> 00:18:26,090
At the entrance...

327
00:18:26,174 --> 00:18:30,390
Disguised themselves as Kanae-san,
and went out walking with Matsunosuke.

328
00:18:31,225 --> 00:18:35,818
To create witnesses who saw
Kanae-san walking Matsunosuke...

329
00:18:35,902 --> 00:18:38,406
And to establish
their own alibi.

330
00:18:39,075 --> 00:18:41,079
Of course, it was an amateur disguise...

331
00:18:41,162 --> 00:18:43,584
So if someone looked closely,
they might have been found out, but...

332
00:18:43,667 --> 00:18:47,675
Having Matsunosuke with them
fooled everyone.

333
00:18:48,009 --> 00:18:50,347
Marking territory in the usual spot...

334
00:18:50,431 --> 00:18:53,228
Picking a fight with a cat in the usual spot.

335
00:18:53,562 --> 00:18:57,946
Everyone thought, "Oh, it's the same old lady
with Matsunosuke, as always."

336
00:18:59,991 --> 00:19:02,914
But when the culprit
left the park...

337
00:19:02,997 --> 00:19:04,876
They went to the right.

338
00:19:05,168 --> 00:19:07,089
Even though she always goes left.

339
00:19:07,674 --> 00:19:11,723
Makes sense. If they completed
the entire walking route...

340
00:19:11,807 --> 00:19:13,978
It would ruin the alibi setup.

341
00:19:14,479 --> 00:19:18,821
After leaving the park, the culprit
returned home with Matsunosuke...

342
00:19:19,238 --> 00:19:23,539
Met with the person they'd called over,
and completed their alibi.

343
00:19:23,622 --> 00:19:27,755
Wait a minute... The dog?
What about Matsunosuke?

344
00:19:28,256 --> 00:19:30,887
Back then, Matsunosuke
was sleeping here, wasn't he?

345
00:19:30,970 --> 00:19:32,599
So the culprit couldn't have taken him...

346
00:19:32,682 --> 00:19:34,603
It was a fake.
Ha!

347
00:19:34,936 --> 00:19:37,650
The one put to sleep with drugs
back then...

348
00:19:37,734 --> 00:19:41,115
Was a fake Matsunosuke
prepared by the culprit.

349
00:19:41,533 --> 00:19:42,994
...Which means the culprit...

350
00:19:43,077 --> 00:19:46,042
Owns a dog
that looks exactly like Matsunosuke.

351
00:19:46,375 --> 00:19:50,843
Lady, you said you own
one of Matsunosuke's siblings.

352
00:19:50,927 --> 00:19:52,805
Identical to Matsunosuke.

353
00:19:53,181 --> 00:19:56,480
In other words, the culprit
can only be you.

354
00:19:56,563 --> 00:19:58,233
Hirota Tomoko-san.

355
00:19:58,484 --> 00:20:00,362
Conan-kun!
What?!

356
00:20:00,863 --> 00:20:04,161
D-Detective! Please help me!

357
00:20:04,245 --> 00:20:07,042
These children suddenly started
saying the strangest things!

358
00:20:08,002 --> 00:20:10,925
Mouri-kun contacted me,
so I came over, but...

359
00:20:11,259 --> 00:20:13,179
Yeah. Kogoro-san...

360
00:20:13,263 --> 00:20:16,687
Had something urgent come up
and couldn't make it, so...

361
00:20:16,770 --> 00:20:19,442
He asked us to tell you
in his place, Inspector.

362
00:20:19,693 --> 00:20:23,366
I see...
...So, you have evidence, I take it?

363
00:20:23,450 --> 00:20:27,584
Th-That's right! Evidence!
Show me your evidence!

364
00:20:27,959 --> 00:20:29,963
The evidence is right there.

365
00:20:30,046 --> 00:20:31,048
What?

366
00:20:31,132 --> 00:20:33,512
The real Matsunosuke...

367
00:20:34,472 --> 00:20:36,977
That you swapped with your own dog.

368
00:20:37,311 --> 00:20:39,858
What do you have to say,
Hirota-san?

369
00:20:39,941 --> 00:20:42,780
N-No... You're wrong!

370
00:20:42,864 --> 00:20:44,325
This is my dog!

371
00:20:44,659 --> 00:20:46,747
Matsunosuke is
tied up over there...

372
00:20:46,830 --> 00:20:50,337
Hey, Matsunosuke! Let's go!

373
00:20:50,420 --> 00:20:51,673
(dog barks)

374
00:20:52,299 --> 00:20:53,301
Got it!

375
00:20:54,053 --> 00:20:55,431
Ah... Ahh...

376
00:20:58,812 --> 00:21:00,315
We did it!

377
00:21:03,697 --> 00:21:05,200
Hey, lady.

378
00:21:06,410 --> 00:21:10,043
You think the dog is the reason
you got caught, don't you?

379
00:21:10,335 --> 00:21:11,963
Because that's true, isn't it?

380
00:21:12,047 --> 00:21:14,636
If that stupid dog hadn't
gotten lured by a frisbee...

381
00:21:14,719 --> 00:21:15,971
Wrong.

382
00:21:16,932 --> 00:21:19,771
After you killed Kanae-san...

383
00:21:19,854 --> 00:21:22,694
You cleaned up the breakfast,
dressed her in the coat...

384
00:21:22,777 --> 00:21:26,535
And staged it to look like she was killed
after returning from her walk...

385
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:29,582
But you made
a huge mistake.

386
00:21:31,586 --> 00:21:33,005
Kanae-san always...

387
00:21:33,089 --> 00:21:36,011
Had her breakfast after
coming back from the walk.

388
00:21:36,095 --> 00:21:37,097
What?

389
00:21:37,347 --> 00:21:40,395
So if she'd been killed
right after coming home...

390
00:21:40,479 --> 00:21:43,652
The breakfast setup should have been
left as it was...

391
00:21:43,902 --> 00:21:46,950
And if she'd been killed
after eating breakfast...

392
00:21:47,033 --> 00:21:49,956
It makes no sense for her to be
wearing her walking coat.

393
00:21:51,041 --> 00:21:53,004
In other words, that scene...

394
00:21:53,087 --> 00:21:56,762
Was full of inconsistencies
that didn't add up at all.

395
00:21:59,057 --> 00:22:05,069
♪~

396
00:23:13,457 --> 00:23:18,759
~♪

397
00:23:19,384 --> 00:23:22,265
Still, I'm glad...
They found the real culprit.

398
00:23:22,349 --> 00:23:25,814
Now Shinpei-san can
teach us frisbee again.

399
00:23:25,898 --> 00:23:28,277
Yeah... I can't wait.

400
00:23:28,612 --> 00:23:31,283
And your clothes came back
all clean too.

401
00:23:31,743 --> 00:23:34,916
Ah... Matsunosuke's paw prints
got cleaned off...

402
00:23:34,999 --> 00:23:36,544
Nice and clean, good as new...
(Matsunosuke barks)

403
00:23:36,628 --> 00:23:37,964
Gwah!

404
00:23:38,507 --> 00:23:39,968
Ahh...

405
00:23:41,053 --> 00:23:43,767
Ah... Sorry, Conan-kun!

406
00:23:43,850 --> 00:23:46,481
I'll get it cleaned again!

407
00:23:47,148 --> 00:23:49,487
No... that's quite alright.

408
00:23:52,325 --> 00:23:56,083
Here, Detective.
For now, please take this.

409
00:23:57,670 --> 00:24:01,051
He lost the ability to distinguish reality
and became a shut-in...

410
00:24:01,135 --> 00:24:03,389
And in the end,
he went and hanged himself.

411
00:24:03,473 --> 00:24:05,477
Ah... Ahh...

412
00:24:09,610 --> 00:24:12,073
Th-The chief... He won't wake up...
He looks dead!

413
00:24:12,407 --> 00:24:15,246
This one really is dead.

414
00:24:16,021 --> 00:24:17,421
Next Conan,

415
00:24:17,421 --> 00:24:20,421
"Kogoro is at the Bar (Part 1)"

416
00:24:37,021 --> 00:24:39,421
Next Conan's Hint:

417
00:24:39,421 --> 00:24:41,421
"Champagne"

418
00:24:41,635 --> 00:24:42,721
What's
champagne? 

419
00:24:42,804 --> 00:24:44,808
Champagne is something
you drink to celebrate.

420
00:24:44,891 --> 00:24:46,478
Way too fancy
for the old man.
